		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12001.mp3"><![CDATA[The marine environment refers to]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12002.mp3"><![CDATA[all living and non-living things that exist naturally in the Earth’s seas.]]></block2>
		</item>
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12003.mp3"><![CDATA[An ecosystem is]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12004.mp3"><![CDATA[a natural unit consisting of all plants, animals and micro-organisms in that unit.]]></block2>
		</item>
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12005.mp3"><![CDATA[The word “habitat” means]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12006.mp3"><![CDATA[an ecological or environmental area inhabited by a particular animal or plant species.]]></block2>
		</item>		
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12007.mp3"><![CDATA[The IMO aims]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12008.mp3"><![CDATA[to regulate shipping at international level.]]></block2>
		</item>		
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12009.mp3"><![CDATA[MARPOL is aimed at preventing]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12010.mp3"><![CDATA[pollution of the sea by ships.]]></block2>
		</item>		
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12011.mp3"><![CDATA[Climate change is used to refer]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12012.mp3"><![CDATA[to major changes in the weather conditions on Earth, caused by natural events or human activities.]]></block2>
		</item>		
		<item>
			<block1 audio="me12013.mp3"><![CDATA[Greenhouse gases are gases]]></block1>
			<block2 audio="me12014.mp3"><![CDATA[which trap heat above the Earth causing the planet to warm up.]]></block2>
		</item>		
